It's <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>NOT</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> like nerfing a single overpowered ability or item, nerfing the mitigation of a class is nerfing the way a class works, it's changing EVERYTHING about a class in one nerf.  (which is a MUCH bigger and far reaching thing than say the original paladin nerf idea, which was only ONE aspect and yet look at the uproar over that)<br>
<br>
<br>
