<br>
<br>
A lot of things change when you nerf something so integral to a class and don't re-balance them (more avoidance, more damage etc.) in some way.<br>
<br>
<br>
You can't just nerf something like that and expect that to be it, nerfing the WAY A CLASS WORKS, requires careful <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>thought</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> (something VI haven't really done) and that the class needs to be looked at and rebalanced after the nerf. <br>
